{'mcp_link': 'https://mcp.so/server/%E5%8D%A6%E5%8A%A8%E4%B9%BE%E5%9D%A4/hexapulse/NortonHuang?tab=comments', 'mcp_name': '卦动乾坤/hexapulse', 'mcp_author': 'NortonHuang', 'mcp_des': 'HexaPulse is a lightweight MCP service based on the ancient principles of the I Ching\'s Six Yao system, designed to offer users a convenient and swift divination experience. Key Features: Effortless Divination, Anytime: Users can easily perform divinations through the MCP client without the need for traditional tools. User-Friendly Interface: The intuitive design ensures that even beginners can navigate and utilize the service with ease. Six Yao Principles, In-Depth Insights: The system provides interpretations based on the dynamic interplay of yin and yang within the hexagrams, offering guidance for the future. Embark on a journey where ancient wisdom meets modern innovation, gaining clarity and foresight into your life\'s path. Six Yao is a traditional Chinese divination method rooted in the I Ching (Book of Changes). It involves analyzing a hexagram—a figure composed of six stacked horizontal lines, each representing either Yin (broken line) or Yang (solid line). These lines are read from bottom to top, with each line (called a "yao") providing insight into different aspects of a situation. The combination of these lines results in one of 64 possible hexagrams, each associated with specific meanings and interpretations. In Six Yao divination, each of the six lines in a hexagram is analyzed individually and in relation to the others. The position of each line (from the first at the bottom to the sixth at the top) corresponds to different elements of a situation, such as the subject, object, and various influences. Some lines may be "moving," indicating change, which leads to the formation of a second hexagram that reflects the potential outcome or evolution of the situation. Six Yao divination offers a nuanced and dynamic approach to understanding complex situations. By examining the interplay of Yin and Yang lines and their positions, practitioners can gain insights into personal decisions, relationships, career paths, and more. It encourages reflective thinking and can serve as a valuable tool for personal growth and decision-making. 卦动乾坤是一款基于《易经》六爻原理的轻量级MCP服务，旨在为用户提供简便、快速的起卦体验。 主要特色： 轻松起卦，随时随地：用户可通过MCP客户端，轻松完成起卦过程，无需传统工具。 简洁界面，友好体验：直观的界面设计，使得初学者也能快速上手，享受占卜的乐趣。 六爻原理，深入解读：系统基于六爻的阴阳变化，提供卦象解读，助您洞察未来。 让我们一同探索古老智慧与现代科技的交汇点，洞察未来，掌握命运。 会中文肯定对起卦不陌生。', 'mcp_language': '', 'mcp_time': 'a month ago'}
{'mcp_link': 'https://mcp.so/server/bazi/John?tab=comments', 'mcp_name': 'Bazi', 'mcp_author': 'John', 'mcp_des': '输入出生的时间及地点，调用mcp即可获取排盘好的八字信息及大运流年信息。 二进制文件获取：https://github.com/justinwongcn/bazi-mcp/releases API 获取：https://doc.yuanfenju.com/ MCP tools 输入参考：https://doc.yuanfenju.com/bazi/paipan.html 支持的省市列表：https://yuanfenju.com/zhuanti/detail/id/117.html 调用示例：请你帮我分析一下，公历2000年1月2日3点4分出生于海南省文昌的男性在2025年的运势如何', 'mcp_language': '', 'mcp_time': 'a month ago'}
